@Jonathan
My personal Rubicon is 'Amirite', especially because it is always accompanied by an obnoxious supercilious need to reinforce the question.
But I can live with 'anyways'. It's not proper English (yes, I am a Prescriptivist) but the added S is a common form of faux-ruralization. No worse than anyhoo.

@Lewis

Here's wishing you a successful surgery, and a speedy and full recovery. 💕
